<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12149e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12149e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12149e"> 149(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> culte de S. Orient / (soleil) / Lausanne</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Un peu plus loin, dans le pays de Gen&egrave;ve, un autre culte h&eacute;t&eacute;rodoxe marquait encore le recul de la vie <font color="green">[180]</font> catholique: c&apos;&eacute;tait le culte du Soleil ou Saint-Orient. <br> &hellip; <font color="green">[Quoting a letter of Vincent]</font> &ldquo;Je me dispose &agrave; visiter le dioc&egrave;se de Lausanne, o&ugrave; l&apos;on adore aussi publiquement le soleil, surtout &agrave; la campagne.&rdquo; <br><font color="green">[A bit further, in the land of Geneva, another heterodox cult marked the retreat of Catholic life: <mark>the cult of the Sun or Saint-Orient</mark>.]</font> <br> &hellip; <font color="green">[&lsquo;I am preparing to visit the diocese of <mark>Lausanne</mark>, where the sun is also publicly worshipped, especially in the countryside.&rsquo;]</font> <small> Matthieu-Maxime Gorce, <a name="STVF" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#STVF"><cite title="source">Saint Vincent Ferrier</cite></a> (1924) 180-1</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
